<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1271,436,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
– Widely distributed in the eastern Palaearctic Region. New to the fauna of 
<collectingCountry name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1271,436,1782]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">– Deviating features: (1) antenna with (18–)20–22(–24) antennomeres; (2) first tergite 1.3–1.5 times length of hind width; (3) body dark coloured with first tergite reddish yellow, meso- and metasoma variably reddish yellow to testaceous, head and mesoscutum usually dark coloured.</paragraph>
